<section id="development-cycle">
<title>Development Stages</title>

<para>
The following is a high level description of the Inca component development
cycle.  Where appropriate steps are automated.  The automation is explained in
tools.
</para>

<procedure>
<title>Inca Release Stages</title>
<step>
<para>Normal development.</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>Code freeze happens and cleanup cycle begins.  NO NEW FUNCTIONALITY!</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>Developer believes their code is ready for release.  Create a release
candidate.</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>Code reviews and testing by other team members.  This can result in
rejection of the release candidate or small updates/changes to the candidate.</para>
</step>
<step>
<para>
The entire team agrees that the code is ready for release.  So it is released.
</para>
</step>
</procedure>

<para>
</para>
</section>
